    "body": "[feat] improve argmax kernel for greedy sampling in gptoss with eagle speculative decoding.\r\n \r\ndefault torch.argmax used in greedy speculative heads takes about 15us with memset call preceding it. \r\nnew cute dsl based argmax kernel improves kernel time from ~15 -> 4 us \r\n\r\nin eagle3 spec decode, e2e Q0.5 TPS improves by about 15-20 TPS at BS=1\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n## Release Notes\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Introduced a specialized, high-performance kernel for efficiently computing maximum values and corresponding indices across tensors, delivering improved throughput for tensor reduction operations.\n\n* **Improvements**\n  * Integrated optimized kernel selection mechanism into speculative token generation workflows, enhancing inference performance.\n\n* **Chores**\n  * Added license information for the Quack project to the LICENSE file.\n\n<sub>✏️ Tip: You can customize this high-level summary in your review settings.</sub>\n\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
